The paper deals with analyzing video frames using machine learning techniques, specifically Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs). This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also proposes a novel bio-inspired methodology for analyzing video frames, which involves Bayesian update and rational prediction, indicating a focus on machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.LG, cs.AI). The paper also discusses the suitability of using different CNN models in multi-processor systems-on-chips (MPSoCs), which falls under the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. Finally, the paper introduces a new metric for assessing the energy consumption of using CNN models, which could fall under the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
